-- TRW plans to open technical centre in China by 2013
-- 
-- Tue Apr 19, 2011 10:55pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/04/20/us-autoshow-trw-idUSTRE73J0H320110420

 

 SHANGHAI  (Reuters) - TRW Automotive Holdings Corp ( TRW.N ), a U.S. automotive supplier, plans to open a new technical center in China for more than 1,000 engineers when it opens in 2013. 

 The center would be built Anting, on the outskirts of Shanghai, the company said in a release. Based in Livonia, Michigan, TRW makes auto safety equipment such as airbags and electronic stability control systems. It is ranked among the top 10 automotive suppliers globally. (Reporting by Alison Leung; Editing by Chris Lewis)